kground:#4ee633|\n| ''Mickey's Great Outdoors''\n| 1\u20133\n| 5\n| May 24, 2011\n| 90, (\"The Go-Getters\"), 38 (\"Mickey and Minnie's Jungle Safari\"), 39 (\"Mickey's Camp Out\"), 78 (\"Daisy's Grasshopper\") and 88 (\"Mickey's Fishy Story\")\n|-\n| style=\"background:#030d31|\n| ''Space Adventure''\n| 3\n| 2\n| November 8, 2011\n| 89 (\"Space Adventure\") and 94 (\"Goofy's Thinking Cap\")\n|-\n| style=\"background:#f2b3d0|\n| ''I Heart Minnie''\n| 1\u20133\n| 5\n| February 7, 2012\n| 8 (\"Minnie's Birthday\"), Episode 11 (\"Daisy's Dance\"), 40 (\"Daisy's Pet Project\"), 53 (\"Minnie's Rainbow\") and 95 (\"Minnie and Daisy's Flower Shower\")\n|-\n| style=\"background:#54bc65|\n| ''Mickey and Donald Have a Farm''\n| 1\u20134\n| 5\n| December 11, 2012\n| 23 (\"Goofy's Petting Zoo\"), 29 (\"Goofy the Homemaker\"), 52 (\"Clarabelle's Clubhouse Mooo-sical\"), 98 (\"Donald Hatches an Egg\") and 100 (\"Mickey and Donald Have A Farm\")\n|-\n| style=\"background:#0186c9|\n| ''Minnie's the Wizard of Dizz''\n| 3, 4\n| 4\n| February 5, 2013\n| 91 (\"Goofy's Gone\"), 99 (\"The Golden Boo Boo\") and 104 (\"Minnie's the Wizard of Dizz\")\n|-\n| style=\"background:#e48d40|\n| ''Quest for the Crystal Mickey''\n| 2\u20134\n| 5\n| May 21, 2013\n| 59 (\"Goofy's Coconutty Monkey\"), 71 (\"Donald of the Desert\"), 77 (\"Donald the Genie\"), 85 (\"Goofy's Giant Adventure\") and 101 (\"Quest For the Crystal Mickey\")\n|-\n| style=\"background:#e7d3b8|\n| ''Super Adventure!''\n| 3, 4\n| 4\n| December 3, 2013\n| 79 (\"Mickey's Mousekersize\"), 80 (\"Mickey's Little Parade\"), 97 (\"Aye, Aye, Captain Mickey\") and 105 (\"Super Adventure\")\n|-\n| style=\"background:#00a54b|\n| ''Around the Clubhouse World''\n| 1\u20134\n| 5\n| February 11, 2014\n| 5 (\"Donald and the Beanstalk\"), 9 (\"Goofy On Mars\"), 30 (\"Mickey's Handy Helpers\"), 74 (\"Pluto's Dinosaur Romp\") and 115 (\"Around the Clubhouse World\")\n|-\n|}\n\n==Production==\nMickey Mouse was originally voiced by Wayne Allwine with Bret Iwan taking over the role following Allwine's death in 2009. The final episode to feature Allwine as Mickey aired posthumously in 2011. [[Bill Farmer]], the voice actor for Goofy and Pluto, stated in February 2014 that the recording of dialogue for new episodes has ceased, but that \"it will be quite a while before the show runs out of new episodes for TV. We have been on the air consistently since 2006 and we started recording in 2004. So there is always a long lead-in time between recording and seeing it on TV. So don\u2019t worry more is still to come, we just are not making any more.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mediamikes.com/2014/02/disney-legend-bill-farmer-talks-about-voicing-goofy-and-new-series-the-7d/ |author=Mike Gencarelli |publisher=Media Mikes |title=Disney Legend, Bill Farmer talks about voicing Goofy and new Disney Junior series \"The 7D\" |accessdate=November 10, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n''Mickey Mouse Clubhouse'' received mixed to positive reviews, [[Common Sense Media]] rated the show a 4 out of 5 stars, stating: \"Parents need to know that ''Mickey Mouse Clubhouse'' is a lively series designed to help preschoolers acquire problem-solving and early mathematics skills \u2013 and does so in a fun, exciting way. Although the show is very learning-focused, it's engaging without being intimidating.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.commonsensemedia.org/tv-reviews/mickey-mouse-clubhouse|title=Mickey Mouse Clubhouse - TV Review|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n==Spin-offs==\n\n===''Minnie's Bow-Toons''===\n{{main|Minnie's Bow-Toons}}\n''[[Minnie's Bow-Toons]]'' is a [[spin-off (media)|spin-off]] series which premiered in the fall of 2011 and concluded in 2016. It aired in the daytime Disney Junior programming block for younger audiences. It is based on the ''Mickey Mouse Clubhouse'' episode \"Minnie's Bow-tique\" and depicts Minnie's continuing adventures in business as proprietor of her own store which makes and sells bows for apparel and interior decoration. She interacts with many of the characters seen in the ''Mickey Mouse Clubhouse'' series.\n\n===''Mickey Mouse Mixed-Up Adventures'' (originally known as ''Mickey and the Roadster Racers'')===\n{{main|Mickey Mouse Mixed-Up Adventures}}\nA second spin-off, ''[[Mickey Mouse Mixed-Up Adventures|Mickey and the Roadster Racers]]'', debuted in January 2017 after Mickey Mouse Clubhouse stopped showing episodes in November 2016.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Events|first1=Fathom|title=Celebrate \u2018Disney Junior at the Movies\u2019 and be Among First to See the New Series Mickey and the Roadster Racers, in Cinemas for One Day|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20161013005389/en/Celebrate-%E2%80%98Disney-Junior-Movies%E2%80%99-Series-Mickey-Roadster|website=Business Wire|accessdate=13 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/mickey-and-the-roadster-racers-disney-junior-watch-video-1201468449/|title=Watch: \u2018Mickey and the Roadster Racers\u2019 to Debut on Disney Junior in 2017|last=Wagmeister|first=Elizabeth|website=Variety|language=en-US|access-date=21 March 2016}}</ref> It was renamed ''Mickey Mouse: Mixed Up-Adventures'' for the third season.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{notelist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Portal|Cartoon}}\n* {{official website|http://disneyjunior.disney.com/mickey-mouse-clubhouse}}\n* {{IMDb title|0784896}}\n* {{bcdb |Walt_Disney_Studios/Television/Mickey_Mouse_Clubhouse/ |Mickey Mouse Clubhouse }}\n* {{tv.com show|disneys-mickey-mouse-clubhouse}}\n{{Mickey Mouse cartoons}}\n{{TV series and movies set in the Mickey Mouse universe}}\n{{Disney Junior}}\n{{Playhouse Disney}}\n\n[[Category:Articles needing additional references from June 2017]]\n[[Category:2006 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2016 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:2000s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:American animated television programs featuring anthropomorphic characters]]\n[[Category:American children's animated adventure television series]]\n[[Category:American children's animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:American children's animated fantasy television series]]\n[[Category:American children's animated musical television series]]\n[[Category:American preschool education television series]]\n[[Category:American computer-animated television series]]\n[[Category:Disney Junior shows]]\n[[Category:Donald Duck television series]]\n[[Category:Family Channel shows]]\n[[Category:Mickey Mouse television series]]\n[[Category:Television series by Disney Television Animation]]\n[[Category:American animated television spin-offs]]\n", "name_user": "Enes Veliq", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eHome media", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mickey_Mouse_Clubhouse"}
{"title_page": "Akhil (singer)", "text_new": "{{notability|Biographies|date=March 2019}}\n{{short description|Indian singer, songwriter and music composer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date = March 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date = March 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Akhil\n| image            = \n| caption          = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| alias            = Akhil Pasricha\n| birth_date       = \n| birth_place      = \n| origin           = \n| genre            = [[Pop music|Pop]], [[Hip hop music|Hip Hop]], [[Bhangra (music)|Bhangra]]\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n* Actor\n* Singer\n* Songwriter\n* Music composer\n}}\n| instrument       = \n| years_active     = 2013\u2014present\n| label            = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]<br>Tru Makers<br>Speed Records<br>Crown Records\n| associated_acts  = [[Ikka Singh|Ikka]]<br>[[Adah Sharma]] [[Manni Sandhu]]\n| website          = {{url|http://facebook.com/Akhil Official01}}<br>{{url|http://instagram.com/a.k.h.i.l_01}}\n}}\n\n'''Akhil Pasricha''', known mononymously as '''Akhil''',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/delhi/khwaab-singer-akhils-gig-police-thrashing-unruly-crowd-bring-dramatic-end-to-kmc-fest/articleshow/68429109.cms|title=Khaab singer Akhil\u2019s gig, police thrashing unruly crowd bring dramatic end to KMC fest - Times of India \u25ba|website=The Times of India}}</ref> is an Indian actor, playback singer, songwriter and music performer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/topic/Akhil|title=Akhil: Latest News, Videos and Photos of Akhil &#124; Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.patrika.com/bikaner-news/punjabi-singer-akhils-songs-in-bikaner-2010235/|title=\u092c\u0940\u0915\u093e\u0928\u0947\u0930 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092a\u0902\u091c\u093e\u092c\u0940 \u0938\u093f\u0902\u0917\u0930 \u0905\u0916\u093f\u0932 \u0915\u0947 \u0917\u093e\u0928\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u0940 \u092e\u091a\u0947\u0917\u0940 \u0927\u0942\u092e|website=www.patrika.com}}</ref> He made his [[Music of Bollywood|Bollywood singing]] debut in ''[[Luka Chuppi]]'' (2019).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.in.com/entertainment/regional/after-sunanda-punjabi-singers-karan-and-akhil-step-into-bollywood-328701.htm|title=After Sunanda, Punjabi singers Karan and Akhil step into Bollywood|website=in.com}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\n\nAkhil was born on 2 October in 1990 in [[Jalandhar]], [[Punjab]], [[India]]. He completed his school education from \u201cArya Senior Secondary School\" in Nurmahal, [[Jalandhar]]. Then he completed his graduation from APJ College of Fine Arts.{{Citation needed|date=March 2019}}\n\n== Career ==\n\nIn February 2014, his first single \"Muradaan \" was released under HSR Entertainment (formerly Yellow Music).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.catchnews.com/bollywood-news/luka-chuppi-songs-singer-akhil-s-khaab-is-now-kartik-aaryan-and-kriti-sanon-s-duniyaa-150251.html|title=Luka Chuppi Songs: Singer Akhil's 'Khaab' is now Kartik Aaryan and Kriti Sanon's 'Duniyaa'|website=CatchNews.com}}</ref>He previously sang a song titled \"Pee Lain De\" in 2012 though.<ref>{{Citation|title=Akhil Pasricha {{!}} Pee Lain De {{!}} OFFICIAL VIDEO {{!}} 2012|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eyDgXjMylTQ|language=en|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref> \n\nHis Punjabi-language single \"Khaab\", which was released in February 2016 became popular on [[YouTube]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/check-out-kartik-aaryan-kriti-sanons-sizzling-chemistry-in-this-exclusive-still-from-luka-chuppi-song-duniya/370484|title=Luka Chuppi song Duniyaa: Kartik Aaryan and Kriti Sanon's sizzling chemistry will leave you impressed &#124; Bollywood News|website=www.timesnownews.com}}</ref> In February 2019, a Hindi remake of ''Khaab'', ''Duniyaa'', was recorded for the film ''[[Luka Chuppi]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ptcpunjabi.co.in/akhil-steps-into-bollywood-with-khaab-remake-for-luka-chuppi/|title=Akhil Steps Into Bollywood With Khaab Remake For Luka Chuppi|first=Diksha|last=Kapoor|date=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2016, he collaborated with music composer \"[[Manni Sandhu]]\" for a single titled \"Gani\" for his album ''Welcome To The Future'', released by Speed Records.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.in.com/entertainment/regional/akhil-screws-up-his-khaab-by-letting-bollywood-recreate-it-as-duniya-323077.htm|title=Akhil screws up his 'Khaab' by letting Bollywood recreate it as 'Duniya'!|website=in.com}}</ref> A year later, he released the single \"Life\" starring bollywood actress [[Adah Sharma]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://chandigarhmetro.com/life-punjabi-song-by-akhil-heres-the-official-video/|title=Life (Punjabi Song) by Akhil - Here's the Official Video of the New Song|date=16 June 2017|website=Chandigarh Metro}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://chandigarhmetro.com/life-punjabi-song-by-akhil-heres-the-official-video/|title=Life (Punjabi Song) by Akhil - Here's the Official Video of the New Song|date=16 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n\n===Film Songs===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Film\n!Track\n!Co-Singer(s)\n!Label\n!Notes\n|-\n|2016\n|[[Vaapsi]]\n|''Saari Saari Raat'' \n|\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Speed Records\n| rowspan=\"3\" |Punjabi Movies\n|-\n|2017\n|[[Jindua]]\n|''Takdi Ravan''\n|[[Jonita Gandhi]]\n|-\n|2018\n|[[Ishqaa]]\n|''Ishqaa''\n|\n|[[Times Music]]\n|-\n|2019\n|Luka Chuppi\n|''Duniyaa''\n|[[Dhvani Bhanushali]]\n|[[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n|Bollywood Debut\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Singles ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#cfc; text-align:center;\"\n!Year\n!Track\n!Featuring\n!Label\n!Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2014\n|''Muradaan''\n|\n|HSR Entertainment (formerly Yellow Music)\n|\n|-\n|''Supne''\n|\n|HSR Entertainment (formerly Yellow Music)\n|\n|-\n|2016\n|''Khaab''\n|\n|Crown Records\n|''<small>Breakthrough single</small>''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2016\n|''Makhaul''\n|\n| rowspan=\"11\" |Speed Records\n|\n|-\n|''Gani''\n|\n|-\n|''Teri Kami''\n|\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |2017\n|''Zindagi''\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.radioandmusic.com/entertainment/editorial/news/180214-punjabi-singer-akhil-unveils-love-single-on|title=Punjabi singer Akhil unveils love single on V-Day)}}</ref>\n|-\n|''Life''\n|\n|\n|-\n|''Mere Khuda''\n|\n|\n|-\n|''Rukh''\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jagran.com/haryana/kurukshetra-punjabi-singer-akhil-in-nit-and-a-former-student-of-the-institute-is-very-fond-of-future-engineer-on-songs-of-vivek-18587113.html|title=\u090f\u0928\u0906\u0907\u091f\u0940 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092a\u0902\u091c\u093e\u092c\u0940 \u0917\u093e\u092f\u0915 \u0905\u0916\u093f\u0932 \u0914\u0930 \u0938\u0902\u0938\u094d\u0925\u093e\u0928 \u0915\u0947 \u092a\u0942\u0930\u094d\u0935 \u091b\u093e\u0924\u094d\u0930 \u0935\u093f\u0935\u0947\u0915 \u0915\u0947 \u0917\u0940\u0924\u094b\u0902 \u092a\u0930 \u0916\u0942\u092c \u0925\u093f\u0930\u0915\u0947 \u092d\u093e\u0935\u0940 \u0907\u0902\u091c\u0940\u0928\u093f\u092f\u0930|website=Dainik Jagran}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://chandigarhmetro.com/rukh-new-punjabi-song-by-akhil-out-official-video/|title=Rukh (New Punjabi Song) by Akhil Out &#124; Official Video|date=17 August 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|''Bollywood''\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://chandigarhmetro.com/bollywood-by-akhil-latest-punjabi-song-2017-official-video-out/|title=Bollywood by Akhil (Latest Punjabi Song 2017) &#124; Official Video Out|date=16 December 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2018\n|''Akh Lagdi''\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://chandigarhmetro.com/akh-lagdi-by-akhil-ft-desi-routz-new-punjabi-song-official-video-out/|title=Akh Lagdi by (Akhil ft Desi Routz) New Punjabi Song &#124; Official Video Out|date=15 February 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|''Rang Gora''\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/punjabi/music/rang-gora-akhil-creates-a-romantic-buzz-on-the-internet/articles